               <birth when="1872">He was born at <placeName ref="gn:3170831"/> in <date>1872</date>.</birth>
               <floruit  notBefore="1890" notAfter="1949">He was one of the most prominent Ethiopianists of the 20th century. 
                  He started his career as a civil servant in the Treasury of the Italian government. He represented the Treasury in 
                  <placeName ref="LOC5076Paris"/> in the years <date>1908-1910</date> and as a financial expert attended international conferences. 
                  In <date>1914</date>, he became the Secretary-General in the Italian Administration. A decade later, he was named Councillor of the State. 
                  From<date>1920-1949</date>, he held the chair of History  and Languages of Abyssinia in the University of <placeName ref="gn:3169070"/>
                  faculity of Humanities, succeeding his teacher <persName ref="PRS4876Guidi"/>. Besides his official engagements as a civil servant,
                  he profoundly developed his scientific work in the field of the humanities. He won an important place in editing of Ethiopic texts.</floruit>
